, Z000002688).
</paragraph>
</caption>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="71" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="71">Note.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="71">
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Caryophyllaceae" genus="S." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="S. pusilla" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="0" pageNumber="71" phylum="Magnoliophyta" rank="species" species="pusilla">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="71">S. pusilla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described by Schmid based on three specimens &quot; 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="71">Bosshard s.n.</emphasis>
, 25. VII. 1927; 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="71">Bosshard s.n.</emphasis>
, 29. VII. 1927; 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="71">Bosshard s.n.</emphasis>
, 13. VIII. 1927&quot; collected by Bosshard from China, but he 
<normalizedToken originalValue="didn’t">didn't</normalizedToken>
designate one of them as holotype in the protologue. Plants of Central Asia (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1201/b10754" author="Grubov, VI" journalOrPublisher="Annales Botanici Fennici" pageId="0" pageNumber="71" refId="B4" refString="Grubov, VI, Kozhevnikov, YP, 2007. Plants of Central Asia - Plant Collection from China and Mongolia. Science Publishers, 33 pp. https://doi.org/10.1201/b10754" title="Plants of Central Asia - Plant Collection from China and Mongolia. Science Publishers, 33 pp." url="https://doi.org/10.1201/b10754" year="2007">Grubov and Kozhevnikov 2007</bibRefCitation>
) cited &quot;Panggon Toso July 25, 1927 (typus)&quot;. Yet following Art. 9.6 and Art. 40 Note 1 of the ICN (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.12705/Code.2018" author="Turland, NJ" journalOrPublisher="Phytotaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="71" refId="B15" refString="Turland, NJ, Wiersema, JH, Barrie, FR, Greuter, W, Hawksworth, DL, Herendeen, PS, Knapp, S, Kusber, WH, Li, DZ, Marhold, K, May, TW, McNeill, J, Monro, AM, Prad, J, Price, MJ, Smith, GF, 2018. International Code of Nomenclature for algae, fungi, and plants (Shenzhen Code) adopted by the Nineteenth International Botanical Congress Shenzhen, China, July 2017. Regnum Vegetabile 159. Koeltz Botanical Books, Glashuetten. https://doi.org/10.12705/Code.2018" title="International Code of Nomenclature for algae, fungi, and plants (Shenzhen Code) adopted by the Nineteenth International Botanical Congress Shenzhen, China, July 2017. Regnum Vegetabile 159. Koeltz Botanical Books, Glashuetten." url="https://doi.org/10.12705/Code.2018" year="2018">Turland et al. 2018</bibRefCitation>
), none of them can be treated as holotype, but all should be considered as syntypes. Bosshard selected type specimens that were deposited at W and Z (
<bibRefCitation author="Stafleu, FA" journalOrPublisher="Phytotaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="71" publicationUrl="https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/item/103859" refId="B13" refString="Stafleu, FA, Cowan, RS, 1993. Taxonomic literature: a selective guide to botanical publications and collections with dates, commentaries and types. Bohn, Scheltema &amp; Holkema, Utrecht. https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/item/103859" title="Taxonomic literature: a selective guide to botanical publications and collections with dates, commentaries and types. Bohn, Scheltema &amp; Holkema, Utrecht." url="https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/item/103859" year="1993">Stafleu and Cowan 1993</bibRefCitation>
). Three original specimens were traced deposited in Z (Z000002688 digital image!, Z000002689 digital image!, and Z000002690 digital image!). All of them agreed with the collection location and date in the protologue and had a label 
<normalizedToken originalValue="“Typus”">&quot;Typus&quot;</normalizedToken>
and another label &quot;Syntype of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="EM. Schmid, Repert. Spec. Nov. Regni Veg. 31: 41" authorityYear="1932" class="Gastropoda" family="Caryophyllaceae" genus="Stellaria" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Stellaria pusilla" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="0" pageNumber="71" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="pusilla">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="71">Stellaria pusilla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
EM. Schmid&quot; written by Sallucn at the same time. Given its label &quot; 
<taxonomicName authorityName="EM. Schmid, Repert. Spec. Nov. Regni Veg. 31: 41" authorityYear="1932" class="Gastropoda" family="Caryophyllaceae" genus="Stellaria" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Stellaria pusilla" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="0" pageNumber="71" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="pusilla">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="71">Stellaria pusilla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Schmid nov. spes&quot; and its good preservation, the presence of flower and lower part of the plant, Z000002688 is designated here as the lectotype following Art. 9.3 and 9.4 of the ICN (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.12705/Code.2018" author="Turland, NJ" journalOrPublisher="Phytotaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="71" refId="B15" refString="Turland, NJ, Wiersema, JH, Barrie, FR, Greuter, W, Hawksworth, DL, Herendeen, PS, Knapp, S, Kusber, WH, Li, DZ, Marhold, K, May, TW, McNeill, J, Monro, AM, Prad, J, Price, MJ, Smith, GF, 2018. International Code of Nomenclature for algae, fungi, and plants (Shenzhen Code) adopted by the Nineteenth International Botanical Congress Shenzhen, China, July 2017. Regnum Vegetabile 159. Koeltz Botanical Books, Glashuetten. https://doi.org/10.12705/Code.2018" title="International Code of Nomenclature for algae, fungi, and plants (Shenzhen Code) adopted by the Nineteenth International Botanical Congress Shenzhen, China, July 2017. Regnum Vegetabile 159. Koeltz Botanical Books, Glashuetten." url="https://doi.org/10.12705/Code.2018" year="2018">Turland et al. 2018</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
